# Concurrent agent PRs each append their own line to the `## Unreleased` section of the changelog.
# Union-merge keeps both lines when a merge runs the driver — but NOTE: GitHub's server-side auto-merge,
# update-branch, and mergeability check do NOT apply .gitattributes merge drivers (only a LOCAL `git merge`
# does). So a stale PR that branched before a sibling appended its line can still show CONFLICTING on GitHub
# and won't auto-merge; the PM resolves it by re-developing the PR onto fresh main (it re-appends its line).
# Keep this attribute (it helps any local rebase/merge and is harmless), but don't rely on it to make
# concurrent appends conflict-free on GitHub. Changelog stays canonical with no fragment/assembly machinery.
CHANGELOG.md merge=union
